From Dale A Dale Adams Subject Re Adding VRAM to Quadra In article W Stuart Jones writes I want to go from K to M VRAM on my Quadra How many K SIMMS do I need to buy Is the current K soldered on the board or do I need to take out the current VRAM before I add more You need to add two K VRAM SIMMs K VRAM SIMMs will not work in any of the Quadra or Centris machines There is already K of VRAM soldered to the logic board You add the two K SIMMs to this to give you a total of MB Dale Adams